canonical:
  title: 和東州客舍留題
  author: 林惟正
  language: lzh
  text: 回首舊遊成古今荊公 郡樓今日更登臨柳間 平生素有煙霞趣王辟玉 晚歲猶存鐵石心子瞻 獨對靑燈數殘漏朱服 笑呼明月作知音韓駒 塵埃奔走曾無暇蘇易簡 一日安閑直萬金樂夫
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 和東州客舍留題
  author: 林惟正
  language: lzh
  text: 回首舊遊成古今。荊公。 郡樓今日更登臨。柳間。 平生素有煙霞趣。王辟玉。 晚歲猶存鐵石心。子瞻。 獨對靑燈數殘漏。朱服。 笑呼明月作知音。韓駒。 塵埃奔走曾無暇。蘇易簡。 一日安閑直萬金。樂夫。
korean:
  title: 동주 객사에서 유제에 화답하며
  author: 임유정
  language: kor
  text: |-
    옛 놀이를 회상하니 하마 벌써 오래 전 일 형공(荊公)
    오늘 다시 올라왔구나 이 군루에 유간(柳間)
    평생에 노 연하 취미를 가졌더니 왕벽옥(王辟玉)
    늘그막에도 아직 철석 심장을 가졌네 자첨(子瞻)
    푸른 등을 혼자 대해 누수를 세어 보며 주복(朱服)
    밝은 달을 웃으며 불러 친구로 삼아 보네 한구(韓駒)
    먼지 속에 분주히 다녀 여가가 없었거니 소이간(蘇易簡)
    하루의 한가함이 값이 만금이로세 낙천(樂天)
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0160_010_0680&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 夫 : '
    value: 天
english:
  title: Responding in Verse at a Guest House in Dongju
  author: Lim Yoo-jung
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Looking back on old pleasures, they've become ancient history—
    like荆公's own reflection.
    Today I climb this county tower once more,
    among the willows as before.

    All my life I've cherished a taste for mist and mountains,
    as 王辟玉 knew well.
    In my declining years, still this iron and stone heart remains,
    with 子瞻's steadfast spirit.

    Alone before the green lamp, I count the remaining hours,
    as 朱服 kept vigil.
    I laugh and call the bright moon to be my companion,
    joining 韓駒's friendship.

    Rushing through dust and ash, I've had no leisure,
    bound as 蘇易簡 was.
    Yet one day of peace and ease—that's worth ten thousand pieces of gold,
    treasure that 樂天 understood.
  footnotes:
    - This poem is a composite work, each couplet attributed to a different classical poet or literary figure, creating a dialogue across time and tradition.
    - The names in parentheses (such as 荆公, 子瞻, 樂天) refer to famous Chinese poets and scholars whose legacies and sensibilities the author invokes to deepen the meditation on memory, nature, and the value of peaceful solitude.
